A vintage 1960s technical illustration style image showing an intricate mechanical sorting machine with brass gears, conveyor belts, and pneumatic tubes. On one side, colorful geometric shapes (cubes, spheres, pyramids) enter through brass hoppers, while on the other side, the same shapes emerge reorganized and combined into new elegant configurations. The machine features Victorian-era industrial aesthetics with copper pipes, pressure gauges, and spinning flywheels. Warm sepia tones dominate with pops of teal and burgundy. Steam wisps curl from various valves. The composition shows a cross-section view revealing the internal transformation mechanisms, gears meshing precisely to guide and combine the shapes along their paths.
